						<div class="postbody">They exist and different TVs/video devices handle them differently.  Some may cap the illegal colour at its outermost legal point, others might have overloading, wrap-around, who knows?  For example, on my Sharp TV, reds that are too strong change to purple or magenta?  On my video capture card, reds that are too strong become fiery orange, for some reason.</div>

